  "title": "Research Intern",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a meticulous, diligent, and resourceful individual to <strong>evaluate the impact of sustainability projects. </strong>The intern will analyse case studies according to the Steward Leadership framework and identify scalable, sustainable projects that address environmental and social challenges. </p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Review case studies</strong>: Thoroughly evaluate all materials and present findings to the reviewing team.</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Conduct desktop research </strong>on impact metrics, existing regulations, and industry standards to perform robust analysis of case studies.</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Collaborate with manager and teammates</strong>: Work closely with the process manager and teammates to ensure smooth communication and adherence to timelines.</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Assist</strong> in other administrative and research development duties as needed. </li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong>:\n</p><ul><li><strong>Postgraduate students</strong> from a relevant field such as Social Science, Business Administration, Corporate\nSustainability, or Sustainable Development are preferred.</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Attention to detail</strong>: Keen eye for spotting outstanding qualities in case studies and ensuring compliance with\nguidelines.</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Time management skills</strong>: Ability to meet deadlines and manage the review process efficiently.</li></ul><ul><li><strong>Excellent verbal and written communication skills.</strong></li></ul><ul><li><strong>Good team player yet able to work well independently. </strong></li></ul><ul><li><strong>Meticulous, analytical, highly organised and intellectually inquisitive.</strong></li></ul><ul><li><strong>Prior experience in evaluating case studies is a bonus.</strong></li></ul><p><strong>Application deadline</strong>: 30 April 2026</p><p><strong>Internship Period</strong>: 18 May – 25 Jun 26, full time. </p><p><strong>Location</strong>: Singapore; Hybrid (you are required to attend meetings in-person when necessary)</p><p><strong>To apply</strong>: Please submit your resume and a brief cover letter explaining your relevant experience\nto <a href=\"mailto:adelinefoo@stewardshipasia.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">adelinefoo@stewardshipasia.com.sg</a>.</p><p>We look forward to your application!</p><p></p>",
